<doc id="421321" wikidata="Q3354676" url="?curid=421321" title="Operation Canuck">
<text>Operation Canuck was an operation of World War II conducted by the Canadian Captain Buck McDonald and a small team of Special Air Service troopers in January 1945.

Operating in Northern Italy, the team trained and organized Italian resistance fighters. In what has been characterized as a remarkable event, the team&#x27;s partisans captured the garrison of Alba, near Turin.


