<doc id="421349" wikidata="Q7096969" url="?curid=421349" title="Operation Defoe">
<text>During World War II, Operation Defoe was a reconnaissance patrol by 21 men of the Special Air Service conducted from 19 July to 23 August to support the British Second Army in the Argentan area of Normandy.

